      "I‚Äôm also told I am low risk presenting no other issues or complications whatsoever so why would a calcifying placenta (which is meant to happen towards the end of pregnancy) warrant this intervention?",
      "I do my own research, get second opinions and weigh up the risks.",
      "I decide not to go for the additional scan at 38 weeks as the logical conclusion would be that the placenta is calcifying - I know this already - and so continue with my birth plan for natural home birth.",
      "Come towards the end of 39 weeks my midwife asks if I have the go ahead from gynae for natural birth.",
      "After that conversation I suddenly realise I am caught in a whole system of what is medical policy etc etc etc and told if I don‚Äôt go for another scan I will not have the support of back up gynae which then ties the hands of midwife and puts her license at risk.",
      "I‚Äôm told with a calcified placenta, medical policy says induction at 39 weeks - standard ü§Ø.",
      "Oh! Right‚Ä¶ I forgot about the legal implications of me wanting to give birth to my child in the best way I believe.",
      "I forgot that this wasn‚Äôt about my body and my baby and birth... it dawned on me that I was up against a mountain of fear mongering of medical policy.",
      "Having had a traumatic induced birth first time around I was feeling particularly sensitive to being pushed into something for no legitimate cause for concern.",
      "I agreed to go for another scan and as I expected - everything was developing healthy and fine with baby, he had enough oxygen, enough amniotic fluid, showing no signs of distress, growing well - big and strong etc.",
      "The only 'concern' was a 'calcifying placenta' - which happens naturally at the end of pregnancy to signal the body to go into natural labour!",
      "Everything in me said 'No, trust YOUR body, trust your mother instinct'.",
      "Due to the case of the placenta and me asking to be allowed to continue for natural birth, the gynae refused to support my birth. This freaked out my midwife. So I scheduled another meeting with the gynae which I had to pay for! I convinced her to support me and give me another week till 41 weeks (Friday 17th) and offered to sign a disclaimer and state that I was taking the risk and wouldn‚Äôt hold anyone else responsible if anything were to go wrong.",
      "I negotiate to have my birth at Genesis (now no longer because apparently it wasn‚Äôt making enough profit for Life Hospitals as a natural birthing home) instead of home for THEIR peace of mind. They revoked their threat and agreed to support my birth.",
      "A few days go by and by the Wednesday (40 weeks and 6 days) I am 3mm dilated, Braxton Hicks have been appearing for the last week every day and continuing into the evening - I KNOW natural labour is imminent and just need to be left in peace and calm.",
      "But I‚Äôm not given this peace and calm. Thursday arrives just shy of 41 weeks.",
      "I‚Äôm asked by my midwife to come in for an NST at midday. I go - my midwife sends the results to the gynae and checks with the other nurse on duty.",
      "The other midwives and nurses say the reading is fine but the gynae gets back to her and says they‚Äôre not happy with the reading - they want a repeat NST in another hour and I‚Äôm told to bring my hospital bags in case. 'In case of what?' I question. I‚Äôm told because they want to induce labour and possibly go into theatre - I‚Äôm told the gynae has a scheduled C-section at 8pm, so she can do me after that‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs what will be convenient for her.",
      "I am angry and I am scared because I know this is not about my birth and my child and about their schedule.",
      "The midwife seems not to have my back and is being completely compliant with the gynae‚Äôs requests.",
      "I go home and meditate to center myself and calm my anger and prepare for the induction.",
      "I speak to my doula and she says - we will do what we can but it‚Äôs clear they‚Äôre going to do everything they can to get you to C-section.",
      "I channel the fire dragon üêâ. I‚Äôm a big believer in harnessing your animal power in times of need. In my previous birth it was the elephant - this time the fire dragon came to me.",
      "I was raging and I was going to use that to bring my baby into the world.",
      "I surfaced from my center still determined for natural birth with no other intervention, no pain meds, pure.",
      "I prepare my toddler whom I‚Äôve never spent a night away from and tell him what is going on - that I will be home tomorrow with his baby brother - I‚Äôm getting in and out of Genesis as fast as possible. My mom is home to stay with him.",
      "My husband and I leave and I feel like I‚Äôm leaving for battle with a united force with my husband and my doula by my side.",
      "I negotiate with my midwife to take the cytotec in small doses instead of one big whack as in the previous birth. I take the first half dose of cytotec at 4pm.",
      "My doula arrives and we chat, keep the mood light and uplifted despite the situation and tensions with the midwife and gynae.",
