      "I talk to him directly visualising him coming down and always a golden cord from his heart and mine.",
      "Soon after getting onto the floor I feel the urge to push. I keep talking to myself and baby.",
      "The only other voice I am focused on is my doula - her every word of encouragement motivates me.",
      "Each contraction pain makes me feel like I should give up and go to the knife, but her words keep me going. I can do this.",
      "I can hear my husband reassure me every now and then - this opens my heart releases more oxytocin.",
      "I use all of this to open up. With my legs split in squatting position I reach down to touch myself and feel myself opening, to feel my baby, I caress my vagina to my thighs telling myself I am opening wide open, getting huge!.",
      "I tell baby to come into the world. We are ready. I push, I can feel it coming close.",
      "Midwife suggests a position change. I turn around and have my husband on the bed behind me holding me up and I push while breathing the fire dragon imagining my heart opening my whole birth passage opening.",
      "I can feel the burning and I know it‚Äôs close - we are there. I push again and I can feel baby‚Äôs head come out.",
      "I wait for a moment for the next contraction to push the rest of baby out.",
      "Finally. We are there. I open my eyes I hear him scream. I take him into my arms. He is perfect.",
      "It took about 3 pushes to get him out. From induced active labour to birth it took 1h45 +- minutes- I birthed at 9:22pm.",
      "I don‚Äôt know how we managed to go so quickly but having the deadline of a C-section sure put the pressure on.",
      "This is a testament to mind power, to trusting the body, connecting body mind and heart - it can be done.",
      "No tears to my vagina and a perfectly healthy baby at 3.79kgs 55cm long and a marginally calcified placenta. We did it against all odds.",
      "I am eternally grateful to my doula and husband for protecting me in my most vulnerable moment and helping through this passage of birth, giving my son his right to natural birth.",
      "This is not to say C-sections don‚Äôt have a place in saving a baby and mother but it didn‚Äôt have a legitimate place in my case and I am grateful we trusted that instinct and didn‚Äôt give into the pressure just because of what is medical policy.",
      "It was the middle of winter and bloody cold. We spent the rest of the night at Genisis, and when the sun rose we got home as quickly as we could.",
